## Important Notices

### Third-Party Services
This project depends on several third-party services. When using or deploying Cravo, ensure compliance with the terms and conditions of:

- **Cloudinary** – Image hosting and CDN service
- **Razorpay** – Payment processing (PCI-DSS compliant)
- **Resend** – Email delivery service
- **Google Cloud** – OAuth authentication service
- **Render** – Cloud deployment platform
- **MongoDB** – Database service (if using MongoDB Atlas)

Each service has its own terms of service and privacy policies. Users are responsible for reviewing and complying with these terms.

### Data Privacy & Security
This project handles sensitive user data including:
- Personal information (name, email, phone)
- Payment information (processed through Razorpay)
- Address data
- Order history

When deploying or using Cravo, ensure:
- HTTPS/TLS encryption for all data in transit
- Secure storage of API keys and credentials
- Compliance with data protection regulations (GDPR, CCPA, etc.)
- Regular security audits and updates

### No Warranty
THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND. The author makes no representations or warranties regarding the functionality, security, or suitability of this software for any particular purpose.

Users are solely responsible for:
- Testing the software in their environment
- Securing their deployment
- Maintaining backups
- Monitoring for security vulnerabilities

